---
alwaysApply: true
---
MVP feature scope (Phase 1):
- authentication (Google OAuth, `@darulislah.org` only)
- dashboard
- announcements
- document / SOP hub (metadata + external links only)
- quick links
- internal requests / help desk
- Google Calendar events (read-only, synced server-side)
- Jotform submissions viewer (read-only, role/user-granted access)

Explicitly out of MVP scope (defer to Phase 2+):
- vendor directory
- hall booking workflow
- preferred vendor management
- public-facing forms or member workflows
- file uploads / blob storage / S3 integration
- email notification system
- Jotform write-back or submission editing
- two-way Google Calendar sync
- analytics dashboards
- AI-powered features

Enforcement rules:
- build only features listed in MVP scope unless user explicitly changes scope
- do not create routes, tables, or services for deferred features
- keep integrations simple and read-focused for Calendar and Jotform
- preserve "documents are links, not uploads" as a hard boundary
- if a request conflicts with this scope, ask for explicit scope-change approval